The paper deals with the problem of configuration formation in modular robotic systems, which is a topic closely related to robotics and automation (cs.RO). The proposed algorithm is based on heuristic search and aims to maximize the amount of information collected during the configuration formation process, which suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.MA). The problem also involves energy budget constraints and optimization, which are common themes in control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses experimental results and performance comparisons with other algorithms, which suggests a connection to software engineering (cs.SE).
